# Designs

> Detailed designs for Agents Relay Orchestration features.


## Designs

### Auto-Generated Relay Run Titles

#### Title Extraction Algorithm

**Input**: Raw task string (e.g., "Build a simple cache module with get/set/delete operations")  
**Output**: Concise title (e.g., "Simple Cache Module")

**Step-by-Step Process**:

1. **Trim & Normalize**
   ```rust
   let task = task.trim();
   ```

2. **Remove Leading Action Verbs**
   ```rust
   // Common action verbs to strip
   let action_verbs = [
       "build", "create", "implement", "add", "fix", "update",
       "write", "generate", "design", "develop", "refactor"
   ];
   
   let task = task.lowercase();
   for verb in action_verbs {
       if task.starts_with(verb) {
           task = task[verb.len()..].trim();
           break;
       }
   }
   ```

3. **Remove Filler Words**
   ```rust
   let fillers = ["a", "an", "the", "with", "for", "from"];
   // Remove first word if it's a filler
   ```

4. **Extract First Phrase**
   ```rust
   // Split into words, take 3-6 words
   let words: Vec<&str> = task.split_whitespace().collect();
   let phrase_words = words.iter().take(6).cloned().collect::<Vec<_>>();
   
   // Minimum 3 words if possible, fewer if task is short
   let phrase = if phrase_words.len() >= 3 {
       phrase_words[..=2].join(" ")  // First 3 words
   } else {
       phrase_words.join(" ")
   };
   ```

5. **Truncate to Max Length**
   ```rust
   const MAX_TITLE_LEN: usize = 40;
   let title = if phrase.len() > MAX_TITLE_LEN {
       format!("{}...", &phrase[..MAX_TITLE_LEN.saturating_sub(3)])
   } else {
       phrase
   };
   ```

6. **Capitalize Words**
   ```rust
   let title = title.split_whitespace()
       .map(|word| {
           let mut chars = word.chars();
           match chars.next() {
               None => String::new(),
               Some(first) => first.to_uppercase().collect::<String>() 
                   + chars.as_str(),
           }
       })
       .collect::<Vec<_>>()
       .join(" ");
   ```

**Examples**:

| Input Task | Output Title |
|------------|--------------|
| "Build a simple cache module" | "Simple Cache Module" |
| "Fix authentication bug in login flow" | "Authentication Bug In" |
| "Add unit tests for cache module" | "Unit Tests For" |
| "Create user authentication system with OAuth2" | "User Authentication System" |
| "Refactor database connection pool" | "Database Connection Pool" |
| "Implement caching layer for API responses" | "Caching Layer For" |
| "Write documentation for relay spawn tool" | "Documentation For Relay" |
| "Design responsive dashboard UI components" | "Responsive Dashboard UI" |

**Edge Cases**:

| Input | Handling | Output |
|-------|----------|--------|
| Empty string | Return default | "Untitled Relay" |
| Single word | Return as-is | "Cache" |
| All action verbs | Take first 3 words | "Build System" |
| Non-English text | Basic word split still works | "Módulo De Caché" |
| Special characters | Preserve but limit | "Cache: Module" |

#### Rust Implementation

**New File**: `backend/src/relay/title.rs`

```rust
use std::collections::HashSet;

const MAX_TITLE_LEN: usize = 40;
const DEFAULT_TITLE: &str = "Untitled Relay";

/// Generate a concise title from relay task description
pub fn generate_title(task: &str) -> String {
    let task = task.trim();
    
    if task.is_empty() {
        return DEFAULT_TITLE.to_string();
    }
    
    // Step 1: Remove leading action verbs
    let task = strip_action_verbs(task);
    
    // Step 2: Remove leading filler words
    let task = strip_filler_words(task);
    
    // Step 3: Extract first phrase (3-6 words)
    let words: Vec<&str> = task.split_whitespace().collect();
    let phrase = if words.len() >= 3 {
        words[..=2].join(" ")
    } else {
        words.join(" ")
    };
    
    // Step 4: Truncate if too long
    let phrase = if phrase.len() > MAX_TITLE_LEN {
        format!("{}...", &phrase[..MAX_TITLE_LEN.saturating_sub(3)])
    } else {
        phrase
    };
    
    // Step 5: Capitalize each word
    capitalize_words(&phrase)
}

fn strip_action_verbs(task: &str) -> &str {
    let action_verbs = [
        "build", "create", "implement", "add", "fix", "update",
        "write", "generate", "design", "develop", "refactor",
        "make", "set", "get", "delete", "remove"
    ];
    
    let lower = task.to_lowercase();
    for verb in &action_verbs {
        if lower.starts_with(verb) {
            let rest = &task[verb.len()..];
            return rest.trim_start_matches(|c| c == ' ' || c == ':' || c == '-');
        }
    }
    
    task
}

fn strip_filler_words(task: &str) -> &str {
    let fillers = ["a", "an", "the", "with", "for", "from"];
    
    let lower = task.to_lowercase();
    for filler in &fillers {
        if lower.starts_with(filler) {
            let rest = &task[filler.len()..];
            return rest.trim_start_matches(|c| c == ' ');
        }
    }
    
    task
}

fn capitalize_words(phrase: &str) -> String {
    phrase.split_whitespace()
        .map(|word| {
            let mut chars = word.chars();
            match chars.next() {
                None => String::new(),
                Some(first) => {
                    first.to_uppercase().collect::<String>() + chars.as_str()
                }
            }
        })
        .collect::<Vec<_>>()
        .join(" ")
}

#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    
    #[test]
    fn test_basic_extraction() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Build a simple cache module"), "Simple Cache Module");
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_truncation() {
        let long = "Create a very long task description that goes on and on";
        let result = generate_title(long);
        assert!(result.len() <= MAX_TITLE_LEN + 3); // +3 for "..."
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_empty_task() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title(""), DEFAULT_TITLE);
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_single_word() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Cache"), "Cache");
    }
}
```

#### Frontend Component Design

**RelayRunCard.vue** (Updated)

```vue
<template>
  <div class="relay-run-card" :class="{ active: isActive }">
    <div class="run-header">
      <h3 class="run-title" :title="run.task">
        {{ displayTitle }}
      </h3>
      <span class="run-id" :title="run.run_id">
        {{ shortRunId }}
      </span>
    </div>
    
    <div class="run-meta">
      <span class="flow-badge">{{ flowLabel }}</span>
      <span class="status-badge" :class="run.status">
        {{ run.status }}
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>
</template>

<script setup lang="ts">
import { computed } from 'vue'

interface RelayRun {
  run_id: string
  title?: string
  task: string
  flow_id: string
  status: string
  created_at: string
}

const props = defineProps<{
  run: RelayRun
  isActive?: boolean
}>()

const displayTitle = computed(() => {
  // Prefer auto-generated title, fall back to run_id
  return props.run.title || props.run.run_id
})

const shortRunId = computed(() => {
  // First 8 characters for compact display
  return props.run.run_id.slice(0, 8)
})

const flowLabel = computed(() => {
  // Convert snake_case to Title Case
  return props.run.flow_id
    .split('_')
    .map(word => word.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + word.slice(1))
    .join(' ')
})
</script>

