#### UI Display Hierarchy

**List View** (`RelayView.vue` grid):
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Simple Cache Module    [run-abc123] │
│ Post Discovery        ● Completed   │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Title**: Prominent, left-aligned, truncated with ellipsis
- **Run ID**: Small monospace badge, right-aligned
- **Flow + Status**: Secondary badges below

**Detail View** (`RelayDetailView.vue`):
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Simple Cache Module          [Edit] │
│ run-abc123-def4-5678-90ab         │
│ Created: Jan 15, 2025, 10:30 AM   │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Title**: Large, bold, editable
- **Run ID**: Full monospace, smaller
- **Metadata**: Date, flow, status in secondary row

#### Fallback Strategy

**Scenario**: Legacy runs without `title` field

```typescript
// Frontend fallback logic
const displayTitle = computed(() => {
  if (props.run.title) {
    return props.run.title
  }
  
  // Legacy run: generate title client-side
  return generateTitleClientSide(props.run.task) || props.run.run_id
})

// Client-side generation (simpler version)
function generateTitleClientSide(task: string): string | null {
  const words = task.trim().split(/\s+/).slice(0, 4)
  if (words.length >= 2) {
    return words.map(w => w.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + w.slice(1))
      .join(' ')
      .slice(0, 40)
  }
  return null
}
```

**Benefits**:
- Seamless upgrade path — old runs look better immediately
- Server-side generation for new runs (consistent, cached)
- Client-side fallback for legacy runs (best-effort)

#### Character Encoding & Edge Cases

**Unicode Support**:
- Rust strings are UTF-8 by default
- Title extraction works on Unicode boundaries
- Truncation respects character boundaries (not byte offsets)

```rust
// Safe Unicode truncation
if phrase.len() > MAX_TITLE_LEN {
    let truncated = &phrase[..MAX_TITLE_LEN.saturating_sub(3)];
    // Ensure we don't cut in middle of multi-byte char
    let safe_truncated = truncated.char_indices()
        .take_while(|(i, _)| *i <= MAX_TITLE_LEN - 3)
        .map(|(_, c)| c)
        .collect::<String>();
    title = format!("{}...", safe_truncated);
}
```

**Special Characters**:
- Preserve punctuation in title (e.g., "Cache: Module")
- Remove excessive punctuation (e.g., "Build... cache... module" → "Cache Module")
- Handle emojis gracefully (count as single character)

#### Testing Strategy

**Unit Tests** (`backend/src/relay/title.rs`):
```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    
    // Basic extraction
    #[test]
    fn test_simple_task() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Build cache module"), "Cache Module");
    }
    
    // Truncation
    #[test]
    fn test_long_task() {
        let long = "Create comprehensive user authentication system with OAuth2 support";
        let result = generate_title(long);
        assert!(result.len() <= 43); // 40 + "..."
        assert!(result.ends_with("..."));
    }
    
    // Edge cases
    #[test]
    fn test_empty() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title(""), "Untitled Relay");
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_single_word() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Cache"), "Cache");
    }
    
    #[test]
    fn test_non_english() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Créer module de cache"), "Module De Cache");
    }
    
    // Action verb stripping
    #[test]
    fn test_action_verbs() {
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Implement caching"), "Caching");
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Add user auth"), "User Auth");
        assert_eq!(generate_title("Fix login bug"), "Login Bug");
    }
}
```

**Integration Tests**:
- Spawn relay run → verify title in response
- List relay runs → verify all have titles
- Legacy run migration → verify fallback works

**E2E Tests** (Frontend):
- Open Relay view → verify titles display
- Click run → verify detail view shows title
- Edit title → verify persistence

