## D24 bring_in Tool & Chat Handoff
**Status:** proposed
**Module:** `backend/src/forge/tools.rs`, `backend/src/forge/mod.rs`
**Tags:** stack:both, module:chat
**Depends on:** A9, G17

```rust
// forge/tools.rs — BringInTool
pub struct BringInTool;

impl Tool for BringInTool {
    fn name(&self) -> &str { "bring_in" }
    fn description(&self) -> &str {
        "Bring in another agent to handle this conversation. \
         Use when you've classified the user's intent and know \
         which specialist should take over."
    }
    fn is_read_only(&self) -> bool { true }
    fn parameters(&self) -> serde_json::Value {
        json!({
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "target": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "Profession ID of the agent to bring in (e.g., 'advisor', 'coder')"
                },
                "classification": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "enum": ["NEW_GOAL", "REQ_UPDATE", "QUESTION", "DIRECT"],
                    "description": "Your classification of the user's intent"
                },
                "reason": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "description": "Brief explanation of why you're handing off"
                }
            },
            "required": ["target", "reason"]
        })
    }
    fn execute(&self, args: &serde_json::Value) -> Result<serde_json::Value, ToolError>;
}
```

```rust
// forge/mod.rs — HandoffNote (lightweight, for chat only)
pub struct HandoffNote {
    pub from_agent: String,       // "Nicole"
    pub from_profession: String,  // "assistant"
    pub to_profession: String,    // "advisor"
    pub classification: String,   // "NEW_GOAL"
    pub summary: String,          // Agent's summary of conversation so far
    pub warnings: Vec<String>,    // e.g., "No existing specs found for this topic"
}

impl HandoffNote {
    pub fn render(&self) -> String {
        format!(
            "## Handoff Note\n\
             {} ({}) handed off to you.\n\
             **Classification:** {}\n\
             **Summary:** {}\n\
             {}\n\
             Continue the conversation from here — do not ask the user to repeat what was already discussed.",
            self.from_agent,
            self.from_profession,
            self.classification,
            self.summary,
            if self.warnings.is_empty() { String::new() }
            else { format!("**Warnings:** {}", self.warnings.join("; ")) }
        )
    }
}
```

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant N as Nicole (assistant)
    participant T as BringInTool
    participant S as ForgeSession
    participant I as Isaac (advisor)

    U->>N: "I want to add OAuth2 login"
    N->>N: classify → NEW_GOAL
    N->>T: bring_in(target: "advisor", classification: "NEW_GOAL", reason: "...")
    T->>S: set active_profession = "advisor"
    T->>S: inject HandoffNote as system message
    T-->>N: tool result: "Handed off to Isaac (advisor)"
    N-->>U: [handoff card: Nicole → Isaac]
    Note over I: Next streaming turn uses Isaac's system prompt
    I->>I: reads HandoffNote + full conversation history
    I->>U: "I see you want OAuth2. Let me check existing goals..."
```

| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `target` | `String` | Must be in caller's `handoff_to` list, else rejected |
| `classification` | `String` | QUESTION / DIRECT / NEW_GOAL / REQ_UPDATE |
| `reason` | `String` | Free-text explanation, included in HandoffNote |
| `from_agent` | `String` | Display name of calling agent (from AgentConfig) |
| `summary` | `String` | Auto-generated from tool result (LLM's reason field) |

### Validation Rules

1. `target` must exist in `ProfessionRegistry`
2. `target` must be in calling agent's `handoff_to` list (from Profession config)
3. `target` must differ from current `active_profession`
4. On validation failure: tool returns error, LLM continues in current role

### SSE Events

```json
// New event type: agent_handoff
{
  "type": "agent_handoff",
  "from_agent": "Nicole",
  "from_profession": "assistant",
  "to_profession": "advisor",
  "to_agent": "Isaac",
  "classification": "NEW_GOAL",
  "reason": "User wants to add a new feature (OAuth2 login)"
}
```

### Frontend Rendering

The `tool_call` for `bring_in` renders as a HandoffCard instead of a generic tool result:
- Shows "Nicole → Isaac" with arrow icon
- Shows classification badge (NEW_GOAL)
- Shows reason text
- Active profession badge updates to show Isaac

